article.headline: Penn State 58, Bucknell 46
article.story: STATE COLLEGE (AP) -- Jan Jagla scored 17 points to lead Penn State to a 58-46 win against Bucknell Saturday. Penn State (6-5), which trailed 26-25 at the half, opened the second half with an 11-5 run keyed by guard Marlon Smith's seven points and two assists. Penn State led by eight after a Jagla basket at 8:48, and would not trail again. Kevin Bettencourt led Bucknell (3-8) with 16 points, including a long three at the buzzer to give his team the halftime lead. The Bison used 14 players, while the Nittany Lions used just six. Jagla had four blocks and hit a 3-pointer with three minutes left that ended Bucknell's comeback bid. Smith finished with 15 points, three assists and four steals. Ndu Egekeze had 11 points and 10 rebounds. It was Penn State's first game without guard DeForrest Riley-Smith, who left the team earlier this week, citing personal problems unrelated to basketball. He led the team in assists (51) and was second in scoring (13.3 points per game). The Lions now have only nine players on scholarship, including just two guards, both freshmen.
